reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2019-03-19T00:00:00Z","username":"ANONYMOUS1234","date":"2010-03-18T00:00:00.000Z","text":"LOVELY STORE NICE","doRecommend":"false","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/1844114/denver_co/king_soopers.html"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-03-19T00:00:00Z","username":"jaem0803","date":"2009-01-08T00:00:00.000Z","text":"Worst location to shop at I used to love king soopers over all other grocers until I moved to a neighborhood where this location is the closest one to me. On numerous occasions it has been understaffed to a temper boiling level. One evening after I had packed my cart to the brim I arrive to the check out stands and there is not a single person at a register. I go find the lady working the self check out and her only response is oh, they're all on break I ask when one will be back and she says ten minutes and that I could use the self check out! I don't even want to go into how annoying that was considering there is only so much space to place an item until you have to remove a bag and then everything stops till the lady presses an continue button from her computer. Oh and someone comes up to me and says You have WAY too many items to be here and I said politely Im not here by choice mamn. She leaves. By the time I got home and about 20 other customers passed me by ALL, and I mean ALL of my frozen goods were thawed and drippy. Besides the understaffed issue, their shelves are understocked. Produce and meat are slim pickings all the time. The floors, carts, and everything always feel really dirty. I hate going to this place so much that I drive an extra 2 miles out of my way to avoid it when it's just 10 blocks away.","doRecommend":"false","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/1844114/denver_co/king_soopers.html"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-03-19T00:00:00Z","username":"ex worker","date":"2010-09-10T00:00:00.000Z","text":"kingsoopers treat workers bad I use to work at the kingsooopers on evans for 7 months but i quit. I liked working there when i started and then after the 6th month it just went down hill. They love to give lots of hours with low pay. i use to work up to 45 hours in a week and only make 160 at the most so it sucked. The managers treat there employees like there just useless. I had a fellow employee that had requested two weeksoff 6 months ahead to go on a cruise. the week before she was about to leave they told her that she couldnt go they made her work. She wanted to quit but these times these days it is hard to find a job. Well all im saying is dont blame the employees blame the managers there the ones who run everything. I ALSO ENCOURAGE NO ONE TO WORK THERE","doRecommend":"false","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/1844114/denver_co/king_soopers.html"]}]

descriptions: [{"value":"Safeway, located on West 44th Avenue in Denver, is one of more than 1,800 Safeway food and drug stores in the Western, Southwestern, Rocky Mountain and Mid-Atlantic regions of the United States and Western Canada. Its parent company, Safeway Incorporated, is one of the largest supermarket chains in the United States and trades publicly on the New York Stock exchange under the ticker symbol SWY. The Denver store has a deli, bakery, pharmacy, Starbucks, floral department, liquor department, produce department and a fuel station. Customers can choose from more than 2,500 products, including the store s private label brands-Safeway, Lucerne and Mrs. Wright's. Safeway traces its roots to 1914 when the company was founded under the Selig name. In 1925, Selig changed its name to Safeway, and in 1926, was merged with Skaggs stores.","dateSeen":"2017-03-04T00:58:00.000Z","sourceURLs":["http://www.superpages.com/bp/denver-co/safeway-pharmacy-L0115734867.htm"]}]

reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2019-05-14T00:00:00Z","username":"Kamila Przybylski","date":"2009-02-09T00:00:00.000Z","text":"Seattle-based coffee chain lures caffeine addicts with upscale roasts, caramel frappuccinos, shaken iced teas and an extra shot of trendiness. In ShortFor many, getting their daily jolt of java has become a daily morning ritual, and the cardboard cup with its infamous green label is the close companion of every coffee aficionado. Busy baristas work seamlessly behind the bar, juggling orders for their strongly-brewed drips and signature hot and cool beverages. While providing a wide selection of coffee specialties, pastries and various coffee related goods, patrons are invited to settle down in comfy armchairs and enjoy their favorite brews amid the chatter of the laidback yet caffeinated crowd.","doRecommend":"true","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/43329862/lakewood_co/starbucks.html"]}]

If you are looking for unique food items this is the place to go.","rating":5.0,"userCity":"Denver","userProvince":"Colorado","sourceURLs":["http://tripadvisor.com/Restaurant_Review-g33388-d2465048-Reviews-Marczyk_Fine_Foods-Denver_Colorado.html"]},{"dateSeen":"2017-02-18T00:00:00Z","username":"aceyalbert","date":"2006-10-02T00:00:00Z","text":"Alright, I'll admit it: I moved to Uptown for Marczyk's. It was on the top of the list of places in the neighborhood which looked hip enough for this east coast (Miami) transplant. Thankfully, the content lives up to the fascade! The folks at Marczyk's, from the owner to the butcher, are friendly and knowledgable. Though the selection may seem limited, this is not a supermarket. Each item is carefully chosen (in fact, when the chickens at the local egg farm went on strike, there was an apology note for having to sell what another big chain boutique market considers their \\"top shelf\\" eggs). Highlights include the cheese cave, butcher counter, and pre-made section (one of these days, though, this Miami native is going to have to show the Marczyks how to make maduros from plantains, rather than bananas). Though the produce section does generally leave something to be desired, the staff can usually make excellent suggestions to work around any ommissions in their stock. In all, Marzyk's is an incredible, around-the-corner neighborhood market. My frequent shopper rewards there are embarassingly large, so to say I recommend the place is an understatement.","sourceURLs":["http://www.superpages.com/bp/denver-co/marczyk-fine-foods-L0089615738.htm"],"rating":5.0},{"date":"2015-10-28T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2019-11-03T03:58:25.635Z","username":"Morgan D","title":"Worth the money","text":"This specialty market is definitely more expensive than your average market, but it's worth it for many items. In addition to the downgrading of their cheese section, they also decimated their olive selection and the produce is really almost nil. Yes, they have nice agreements with certain local and organic farmers, which is great, but the selection is completely erratic and the prices for what they do still have really can't compete with Whole Foods. Also, the daily soup selection used to be much more inventive and what happened to the smaller containers of the once-excellent gazpacho in the summertime? My friend took a chance on a pastry stuffed with pineapple. All were so yummy we went back the next morning. We specifically picked out items that we did not saw the previous afternoon since we wanted it fresh. (There were still lots of cookies from the prior day.) We bought a turnover, churros, some huge cinnamon scone, and kids picked another cookie. All again were delicious! The only complaint I had was that there were not a lot of labels and when there were labels they were not always correct. For example, they wrote Manzana (apple) on the turnover but when we bit, it was definitely not apple. It was some cheese turnover, which was yummy, but not what I thought we had bought. The food is not spicy enough, but there are several hot sauces on the table to choose from. I had the salmon enchiladas and they were excellent - topped with a vinegary cabbage mixture, on homemade tortillas. Our service wasn't great, but at these prices, the wait staff isn't making much probably. We had empty cocktalks too often for my liking, but the quality and value of the food will keep me coming back. Despite what other reviewers said, I was there from 8-10 on a Saturday night and had no problem getting a table. None at all. Keep your expectations in check and you'll enjoy Mezcal. Cheese wasnt...","rating":2.0,"userCity":"Denver","sourceURLs":["https://www.tripadvisor.com/Restaurant_Review-g33388-d854246-Reviews-Mezcal-Denver_Colorado.html","https://www.tripadvisor.com/Restaurant_Review-g33388-d854246-Reviews-Mezcal-Denver_Colorado.html#REVIEWS"]},{"date":"2007-09-01T00:00:00.000Z","rating":1.0,"username":"lizzie68","text":"I met some friends for happy hour drinks. We ordered a few of the appetizers, one of which was chips and guacamole. What we got was a small plate of Tostitos and a bowl of frozen, clumpy avocado. Guacamole is a basic dish any Mexican place should have a handle on, but Mezcal does not have a clue. What is wrong with the kitchen staff that makes it ok to 1) send out food that is frozen, 2) use pre-packaged frozen quotquotguacamolequotquot and 3) think guacamole is nothing more than an avocado cut into a few big pieces and dropped in a bowl. At the table, we joked that it was a surprise they managed to figure out that the pit should be removed. Hoping it was just an oversight, we mentioned the situation to our server. She just laughed, shrugged and affirmed that the plain, frozen avocado chunks we got were really what Mezcal wanted us to have when we ordered guacamole. Her attitude let us know that she knew it was gross, but that the kitchen was just dumb. She laughed along with us in disgust and didn't even try to sell it. reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2019-05-12T00:00:00Z","username":"Kamila Przybylski","date":"2008-08-09T00:00:00.000Z","text":"Seattle-based coffee chain lures caffeine addicts with upscale roasts, caramel frappuccinos, shaken iced teas and an extra shot of trendiness. In ShortFor many, getting their daily jolt of java has become a daily morning ritual, and the cardboard cup with its infamous green label is the close companion of every coffee aficionado. Busy baristas work seamlessly behind the bar, juggling orders for their strongly-brewed drips and signature hot and cool beverages. While providing a wide selection of coffee specialties, pastries and various coffee related goods, patrons are invited to settle down in comfy armchairs and enjoy their favorite brews amid the chatter of the laidback yet caffeinated crowd.","doRecommend":"true","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/41250192/denver_co/starbucks.html"]},{"username":"Swan Andrews","date":"2010-03-11T00:00:00.000Z","title":"wow what a store","dateSeen":"2017-09-29T00:00:00Z","text":"this safeway has the most wonderful staff in all of denver keep up th good work","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["http://www.yellowbook.com/profile/starbucks_1861157104.html"]},{"dateSeen":"2017-09-02T00:00:00Z","username":"Kamila Przybylski","text":"Seattle-based coffee chain lures caffeine addicts with upscale roasts, caramel frappuccinos, shaken iced teas and an extra shot of trendiness. This was hands down the most disgusting food we have ever had. My family had to throw it all away and order pizza instead...... I also beleive they leave thier food out all day until someone buys it. They dont make fresh stuff through out the day.","sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/new-dragon-4890588"],"dateSeen":"2019-10-26T15:44:00.000Z"},{"date":"2006-05-24T00:00:00.000Z","rating":1.0,"username":"chuddles33","text":"I ordered the 1.50 scoops. I had rice noodles with some mixed vegetables, curry chicken with sliced potatoes and spicy chicken and a Vietnamese spring roll. The rice paper on the spring roll was like a rawhide chewtoy for dogs. I had to use my molars to eat a spring roll. The curry chicken was about as bland as you could make it. It did have a yellow tint to the sauce but that was the only curry thing about it. The spicy chicken had lots of red peppers and was as bland as the curry chicken. The only flavor was the baby corn and celery. If it weren't for those two items it may have been difficult to tell the difference between the two chicken dishes. We had to go to the Safeway to get something with flavor so that we knew our taste buds weren't permanently disabled.","sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/new-dragon-4890588"],"dateSeen":"2019-10-26T15:44:00.000Z"}]

descriptions: [{"dateSeen":"2019-05-20T03:32:58Z","value":"Visit your neighborhood Safeway located at 323 S Broadway, Denver, CO, for a convenient and friendly grocery experience! From our bakery and deli, to fresh produce and helpful pharmacy staff, weve got you covered! Our bakery features customizable cakes, cupcakes and more while the deli offers a variety of party trays, made to order. At the butcher-block youll find an assortment of meat and seafood, even offering sushi in select locations, while the produce department is full of fresh fruits and veggies galore! Shop the floral department for exclusive debi lily design products and services and stop by the pharmacy for specialty care, including immunizations, prescription refills and so much more! Safeway is dedicated to being your one-stop-shop and provides an in-store bank, Coin Star system, and Western Union service in select locations! Further enhance your shopping experience by grabbing a hot cup of coffee at your in-store Starbucks or Seattles Best Drip Coffee and enjoy renting a movie from Redbox. Check out our Weekly Ad for store savings, earn Gas Rewards with purchases and download our Safeway app for just for U personalized offers. For more information, stop by or call (303) 744-8531. Our service will make Safeway your favorite local supermarket!","sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/safeway-540622566"]}]

Great customer service. You’re greeted when you walk in and feel welcomed. I went for lunch and while the place looks a dive in the wall, The reviews were positive for this place. Next, let’s talk food. I had a breakfast smothered and it was not good. I’m not sure what the smothered was but it didn’t appeal to me. The only reason it got 3 stars is because of the customer service. I would not recommend this place based on my visit nor will I be returning","date":"2019-06-02T00:00:00.000Z","sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/el-toro-262714"],"dateSeen":"2019-10-27T02:26:00.000Z"}]

descriptions: [{"value":"Serving Denver since 1923, Oliver's Meat Market has top quality meat and seafood. Oliver's has perfected it's technique, allowing only the finest cuts to be sold to the local residents. name: Spinelli's Market
reviews: [{"username":"DanW440","rating":5.0,"title":"Part of What Makes a Neighborhood Special","text":"This unique little market is truly a gem. The Parkhill neighborhood has been lucky enough to have it for decades and it’s all encompassing charm continues. Many things are updated, at the same time locals can buy staples of many kinds. Perhaps what makes it special most of all is the very good deli. Excellent sandwiches at a good price, Where one can order a sandwich and have lunch at the little tables out front, along with many other items to add and to choose from. I hope it’s around for many more decades because Parkhill surely deserves this and you deserve to make a visit!","date":"2019-09-16T00:00:00.000Z","sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/spinellis-market-506374724"],"dateSeen":"2019-10-26T18:15:00.000Z"},{"username":"denverfoodadventures","rating":5.0,"title":"One of the best sandwiches in Denver","text":"I don't know how I discovered Spinelli's, but I had some time to kill before an event, so I was looking for a new place to try. It's a classic neighborhood market, complete with gourmet foods and really nice staff. But the true stars are the sandwiches; I can genuinely say the Jerry's Classic (Genoa salami, Capicola, smoked ham, provolone, roasted red peppers and house dressing on a ciabattini roll) is one of the best sandwiches I've ever had. Those red peppers were a spectacular addition to the whole thing...I want one right now, dang it! Grab a Topo out of the fridge and sit on their sturdy wooden tables inside, or if it's a beautiful day grab the metal table outside and people watch in the bougie Park Hill Neighborhood.","date":"2019-06-13T00:00:00.000Z","sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/spinellis-market-506374724"],"dateSeen":"2019-10-26T18:15:00.000Z"},{"username":"Hans M","rating":4.0,"title":"Excellent Lunch Place","text":"If you like Italian deli's like I do, you'll really like this place. Generous size sandwiches, friendly staff, and a small eating area if you want to dine in like I did.","date":"2018-10-11T00:00:00.000Z","sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/spinellis-market-506374724"],"dateSeen":"2019-10-26T18:15:00.000Z"},{"username":"N232YGbarbaram","rating":5.0,"title":"OMG slow down and then stop","text":"The sandwiches from the deli are the best try the Albuquerque Turkey and the. Take home some pasta with sausages. You will be so delighted and a hero to your family when it is your turn to cook choose Spinellis market. 23rd and Dexter in Park Hill","date":"2018-05-27T00:00:00.000Z","sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/spinellis-market-506374724"],"dateSeen":"2019-08-02T00:00:00Z"},{"date":"2011-05-18T00:00:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"username":"heartcolorado","text":"I ordered 75 sandwiches for a catered lunch. I found Spinelli's by googling best sandwich shops in Denver. I agree! Placing the order was easy, delivery was on time and the food was excellent. Everyone complimented the sandwiches, cookies and brownies. The sandwiches were fresh, with generous portions of meat and/or veggies, delicious flavors and the bread was yummy. I will most definitely order from Spinelli's again.","sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/spinellis-market-506374724"],"dateSeen":"2019-10-26T18:15:00.000Z"},{"username":"Jesse C","rating":4.0,"title":"Good products...a little overpriced.","text":"Really good deli counter, great service. I go here about once a week for a sandwich or to buy pizza dough. They also make their own mozzarella cheese. Not exactly an East Coast deli but a good facsimile.","date":"2019-02-10T00:00:00.000Z","sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/spinellis-market-506374724"],"dateSeen":"2019-10-26T18:15:00.000Z"},{"username":"leamington_malfoof","rating":5.0,"title":"Bakery & Cafe is awesome!","text":"I'm not sure why there's no separate listing for the bakery and cafe since they are in a different building, across the street from the deli. Anyway, the baked goods are great! I love cannoli and rarely see them around, but Spinelli's has got me covered! My wife likes their egg sandwiches, but I always stick to pastries. Good stuff, reasonable prices!","date":"2018-08-12T00:00:00.000Z","sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/spinellis-market-506374724"],"dateSeen":"2019-10-26T18:15:00.000Z"}]

reviews: [{"date":"2008-09-10T00:00:00.000Z","rating":3.0,"username":"1denver1","text":"Love the ambience and coffee... service is iffy.","sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/st-marks-coffee-house-15247224"],"dateSeen":"2019-10-26T15:43:00.000Z"},{"date":"2007-08-15T00:00:00.000Z","rating":5.0,"username":"aprylstar","text":"Love it! It's rich!","sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/st-marks-coffee-house-15247224"],"dateSeen":"2019-10-26T15:43:00.000Z"},{"date":"2011-01-15T00:00:00.000Z","rating":1.0,"username":"whomever","text":"I was really excited about this place for a while. Cool funky surroundings, always filled with people talking, chillin, reading, working on their laptops. Seems like a great place to hang , read, study... except for one thing, which is that the staff seems determined to communicate, in every way humanly possible, that they could give a crap about their customers. What do they care, when the customers seem to keep coming no matter rude or indifferent they are. The quality of espresso drinks is horribly uneven and often just horrible (they could care less what they serve you), and if it gets a little busy, the baristas will treat you like cattle. The snarky attitude seems to come from the top-- the owner put up what I first thought was a suggestion box (nice caring touch, community, etc) but then I realized it was positioned over the garbage pail and had an open bottom so that when someone put something in the slot, it would drop into the trash. It might have been an amusing joke somewhere else, but there's no joke when everything else here reeks of quotf--k you.quot The last straw, I went in one evening with an older friend, mid 50s, very polite, mild mannered gentlemanly type. While we sitting and talking (and others were reading or studying) , the barista cranked the music.so loud that no one could hear themselves think let alone hold a conversation. All the customers started looking at each other, cringing, rolling their eyes at one another. Some people actually got up and left. My friend asked the barista, very respectfully and politely, if he could possibly turn down the volume just a bit. It's not a libraryquot was the reply, with barely a glance at my friend. I'm done. descriptions: [{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T22:45:03Z","value":"With annual sales revenue of more than 42 billion, Safeway is one of the largest, food and drug retail chains in North America. It is a Fortune 100 company that maintains a network of distribution, manufacturing and food processing facilities. The retail chain operates over 1,750 stores throughout the United States and Canada. Safeway maintains several milk, bakery, ice cream, soft drink bottling, pet food, fruit and vegetable processing, and cheese and meat packaging plants. The retail chain markets its products under the mom to mom, Safeway SELECT, Signature Caf , Priority Pet Care, Basic Red, Primo Taglio, Rancher's Reserve, Lucerne and Bright Green brands. Through its subsidiary, Blackhawk Network Holdings, the retail chain provides third-party gift, prepaid, and sports and entertainment cards to retailers for sale. Safeway offers a range of diapers, nutritional drinks, toiletries and wipes for children. It also manufactures private-label and national brand products for various U.S. and international customers. The retail chain administers a variety of fundraising activities. In addition, it recycles nearly 450,000 tons of materials every year, as well as works in partnership with the Environmental Protection Agency. Safeway has been a recipient of the Champions of Diversity award from Supermarket News.","sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/safeway-455436104"]}]
name: Safeway
reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","text":"This is a good Pharmacy, but the wait is about 45 minutes! This is outrageous and unneeded! Note: I agree with their stringent policies, so beware to not attempt anything here as all persons MIST SUBMIT A PAIN CONTRACT! My patients have done this, but it should be posted as many have spend needless amounts of time waiting!I agree with chronic pain patients needing a Pain Contract from their MDs, but these matters are unlikely to truly assist anyone abusing Meds!MDs feel burdened, as do Pharmacies! The DEA is doing all it can!But let's remember, it is up to the Professionals to ensure all goes as it should and to ensure all are doing what is required by law!This is not helping but hindering! It is still true: addiction is a DISEASE! Let's start treating people with respect and with proper caution and diagnosis, we are responsible for ensuring that they get and partake in Treatment! The Pharmacy should be doing only what it can, and not attempt to penalize people who may be terminally ill!","rating":3.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/safeway-455436104"]}]

descriptions: [{"sourceURLs":["https://www.trip.com/denver/restaurants/novo-coffee"],"value":"NOVO is at the forefront of coffee in Denver. Over the last couple of years roasters have been popping up all over the place, but NOVO has been around since the beginning. They have three locations right now, the best by far being in the Highlands at 3614 W. 32nd Avenue. It just opened, and for you aficionados, it has the first mod bar in the city, third in the state and it looks amazing. More importantly, it pulls a mean shot. It's not a Starbucks type place, there's very few choices beyond your traditional coffee beverages like latte, cappuccino, cortado etc. They focus and you can tell the difference. Also, the roaster does tours and cupping every Friday at noon--definitely worth checkin out."}]

reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2006-07-10T00:00:00.000Z","username":"denverdelish","text":"This place is great - dinner for four for 40! And good ingredients, nothing skimped on. The food is not spicy enough, but there are several hot sauces on the table to choose from. I had the salmon enchiladas and they were excellent - topped with a vinegary cabbage mixture, on homemade tortillas. Our service wasn't great, but at these prices, the wait staff isn't making much probably. We had empty cocktalks too often for my liking, but the quality and value of the food will keep me coming back. Despite what other reviewers said, I was there from 8-10 on a Saturday night and had no problem getting a table. None at all. Keep your expectations in check and you'll enjoy Mezcal. Not the right place for a quiet dinner or a special occasion, but great for a cheap evening out.","rating":4.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/mezcal-1866738"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2006-11-05T00:00:00.000Z","username":"sbissell3","text":"I had heard good and bad about this East Colfax Mexican eatery. My initial reaction was 'why does Denver need another Mexican Resturant' I have lived and traveled in Mexico for over 25 years and have eaten in all of the major districts of the country and I also enjoy and often eat the more typical 'Tex-Mex' or Southwestern US style of Mexican food. I took a friend who has also lived in Mexico and really knows Mexican food and drink. We ordered a Tamal and a Relleno as appitizers to 'test' the kitchen. It passed with high marks, high enough that my friend, who is a real Relleno snob order more Tamals and Rellenos for his main course. He says the Rellenos are the best in Denver and I know he's eaten a lot of them because it's about all he ever orders. I had fish tacos. While many people think these are a coastal food for Mexico, you get them everywhere and these were excellent breaded Talapia with raw onions and an avacado based salsa. I know why some people have complained about this place it is very typical Northern Mexico. It is what you would get in a better family resturant in Northern Mexico and is therefore strange to folks use to the more typical US style of Mexcian food. Don't be put off, this is the real deal.","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/mezcal-1866738"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2010-04-08T00:00:00.000Z","username":"ndrawker","text":"Was not happy with my meal i couldnt get chips and they ignored me tho whole time, for an over priced meal.","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/mezcal-1866738"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2009-12-18T00:00:00.000Z","username":"iheartfoodtoo","text":"It's a shame a place with such a great start is now a crappy bar with crappy food. When Mezcal first opened it actually had a staff that wanted to be there and enjoyed working there - but over the years that has definately changed. The bartenders are boring, uninteresting and have NO personality. Servers are working on their own time - not yours. So if you want good service - go someplace else. I think Mezcal is dying a slow, painful death! Oh - and it isn't a Denver landmark - sorry but you've got to be in business for at least 10 years before you earn that title, not to mention a place that people actually like to go to!","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/mezcal-1866738"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2007-10-10T00:00:00.000Z","username":"ldicker","text":"This was my forth and last time at Mezcal. I read the previous bad reviews but had to see for myself. I was used to a lively atmostphere with unique regional Mexcian fare. The word must be out, the normaly packed house was empty on a Friday night. Started off with a surly waitress who scoffed at my wifes request for a light Mexican beer. We too were served the frozen guacamole. Not sure what was more cool, the waitress or my tamale. Overall a terrible experience. Do not waste you time or .","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/mezcal-1866738"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2006-02-18T00:00:00.000Z","username":"rfr","text":"Despite other reviews, this place is great for brunch. Seven of us ALL disagreed with the negative comments about Mezcal. All five of our different brunch entrs were wonderful. And, no, we didn't drink a single alcoholic beverage. I had the Entomatada. (Cheese, eggs, corn tortillas, bacon, and chili.)","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/mezcal-1866738"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2008-03-22T00:00:00.000Z","username":"JB25","text":"I had a bunch of friends meet me at Mezcal for my birthday. HUGE mistake!! We had the rudest server I have ever encountered in my life. She scoffed at our drink requests. Along with rolling her eyes at us several times throughout the meal. The margaritas were ok. The food seemed similar to a frozen Mexican dinner. Please save yourself the bad experience and go to King Soopers and buy a frozen dinner. Chances are you'll be treated better by the cashiers in the store than any employee at Mezcal.","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/mezcal-1866738"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2010-10-14T00:00:00.000Z","username":"emmloucircle","text":"Like a bad boyfriend, I kept returning over and over hoping that you would get better - that your food, service, or margaritas would bring back that glitter in my eye - make me love you again. Well, it's over, Mezcal. I've been with you for ten years, and I'm done spending a LOT of money on you and waiting for a better experience. The margaritas and your proximity to home were enough to keep me coming back for a while, and then you even changed your mix on me. Time to shut the doors and call it a night. Oh, and take your bartenders and service staff with you.","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/mezcal-1866738"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2010-04-21T00:00:00.000Z","username":"lo la","text":"The trashybartender badly in need of a shower flirted with my husband telling him she was newly single and called me a name I will not repeat because I asked her the ingredients of a dish. Very unpleasant experience. Too bad because I really like the place but doubt I will return.","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/mezcal-1866738"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2008-04-29T00:00:00.000Z","username":"101101001011","text":"THE HEAD CHEF, OR SHOULD I JUST SAY SLOP COOK HAS THE WORST ATTITUDE I HAVE EVER WITNESSED. HE CLEARLY HATES HIS LIFE AND HIS JOB THERE, AN IT SHOWS IN THE POOR QUALITY OF THE FROZEN AND BULK PRODUCTS THEY USE TO COOK WITH. AND AS FOR THE REST OF THE STAFF...HA! JUST GO TO TACO BELL. YOU WILL THANK ME.","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/mezcal-1866738"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2009-02-15T00:00:00.000Z","username":"ChewYourFood","text":"Just wasted 50 of my hard earned money to eat this overpriced garbage. I am so mad that they are getting away with this. We should have read the reviews first, but passed it and it looked cool, so we decided to check it out. DONquotquott WASTE YOUR MONEY!!!!!! PLEASE DONquotquotT EAT HERE! If you are the owner, burn your restaurant down. If you are the cook, please seriously consider another career. Perhaps dog food developer!","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/mezcal-1866738"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2009-11-03T00:00:00.000Z","username":"geniebloom","text":"Truly a Denver Landmark","rating":4.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/mezcal-1866738"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2007-09-01T00:00:00.000Z","username":"lizzie68","text":"I met some friends for happy hour drinks. We ordered a few of the appetizers, one of which was chips and guacamole. What we got was a small plate of Tostitos and a bowl of frozen, clumpy avocado. Guacamole is a basic dish any Mexican place should have a handle on, but Mezcal does not have a clue. What is wrong with the kitchen staff that makes it ok to 1) send out food that is frozen, 2) use pre-packaged frozen quotquotguacamolequotquot and 3) think guacamole is nothing more than an avocado cut into a few big pieces and dropped in a bowl. At the table, we joked that it was a surprise they managed to figure out that the pit should be removed. Hoping it was just an oversight, we mentioned the situation to our server. She just laughed, shrugged and affirmed that the plain, frozen avocado chunks we got were really what Mezcal wanted us to have when we ordered guacamole. Her attitude let us know that she knew it was gross, but that the kitchen was just dumb. She laughed along with us in disgust and didn't even try to sell it. The other items we ordered were edible, but totally generic- like the big box of taquitos from the freezer section at the grocery store. Mezcal should spend less time trying to look edgy for the yuppies and research some quality TV dinners they can substitute for their crp food.","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/mezcal-1866738"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2007-04-10T00:00:00.000Z","username":"denverkarin","text":"I have never encountered a more grouchy, cantakerous group of people in my life! The staff was so rude! They acted annoyed to be serving my friends and I. Both bartenders I encountered were terrible. He ignored me until I practically yelled at him to get anything! And she was a royal witch. Having worked in the service industry there is absolutely no excuse for this kind of treatment!! And to top it all off when the staff felt it was time to leave (well before closing time) they turned up the house music so loud that we couldn't carry on conversation and were forced to leave. Nice decorations though.","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/mezcal-1866738"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2009-06-06T00:00:00.000Z","username":"bagelles","text":"Went to Mezcal last night. Service was very, very average. Nice waitress, but average. My husband and I ordered a vegetarian combo to share and it came out with chicken in it. The toastata was stale and the food was by FAR the WORST Mexican food I've ever had. On top of it, Mezcal is insanely overpriced. A complete waste of money and we came home to eat after we left. I highly recommend going anywhere but here. This place should just serve their over priced drinks and give up on the food.","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/mezcal-1866738"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2007-06-13T00:00:00.000Z","username":"irishqueen","text":"My daughter and son-in-law and I had the worst food and service at Mezcal. When we arrived for lunch at around 12:30pm the place was empty this should have told us something. I ordered the Fish Tacos which were priced at about 12. These 3 tiny, tiny tacos came with less than a mouthful of fish scattered between the three tacos it was a joke! When I pointed this out to the waiter his response was quotquotWhat do you want me to do about itquotquot The rest of the food was very, very marginal in taste and presentation, and the prices were not cheap. There was a complete lack of interest fom the bartender, waiter and the chef. Taco Bell would have been a better choice. name: Carmine Lonardo's Italian
reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2019-05-15T00:00:00Z","username":"dznaughts","date":"2019-05-13T00:00:00.000Z","text":"I really wanted to love this place when I moved into the neighborhood ... but it is truly dissappointing! You will be overcharged for old, stale, mediocre crap. And you may get the bonus of being ridiculed in front of everyone for the owner's amusement. It has the look and feel of a place that someone really cared about a looooong time ago. Now it looks and feels like no one really cares, like the owner is just going through the motions with the same old, same old. It is very expensive and the quality is a mixed bag. I've bought pounds of desserts and cookies and they were TERRIBLE. 15.99/lb and Every cookie was stale and tasted like the inside of the old, stale fridge case they are kept in (they try wrapping them in plastic wrap, but they all still taste the same - stale. I've ordered sandwiches quite a few times and have gotten really stale hard bread on a couple of them. REally sucks on a 15 sandwich I've tried prepared items out of their deli case and they seemed to taste like the dirty old fridge they are kept in. I just don't have the courage to order anything like the meat, steaks or cold cuts to try. REcently, I went in to order a couple of sandwiches and the owner (first time he ever served me) kept up an uncomfortable running dialogue about not serving people who want mayonaise on a sandwich. He spent 20 minutes ridiculing my taste, my choices, telling stories about kicking someone out, like me, who wanted mayo on a sandwich. He had a great time snickering to his other employees, making jokes for the other 5 customers to laugh at ... all at my expense. Over and over, talking about mayo while i tried to laugh it off and joke too. But he kept going even after all the other customers were not laughing and were looking at me uncomfortably. He just wouldn't stop. I guess he doesn't get the opportunity to bully people elswhere and does it to his own customers!! This guy thinks he's the soup nazi of subs, ferchrissakes. And he is NOT funny. And the food is NOT that good. Definitely NOT worth the money. I considered walking out while he was making the freakin things, but decided I'd see how far he'd take it, then share his inappropriate, unprofessional, dickhead behavior with everyone! And he took it all the way. So, you decide if you want to get ripped off with old stale product and made fun of to boot. I'd rather go to Tommy's Subs, cheaper, better and friendlier, but not open on Mondays. -)","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/1857478/lakewood_co/carmine_lonardo_s_italian.html"]}]

reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2019-05-16T00:00:00Z","username":"Kamila Przybylski","date":"2008-08-09T00:00:00.000Z","text":"Seattle-based coffee chain lures caffeine addicts with upscale roasts, caramel frappuccinos, shaken iced teas and an extra shot of trendiness. In ShortFor many, getting their daily jolt of java has become a daily morning ritual, and the cardboard cup with its infamous green label is the close companion of every coffee aficionado. Busy baristas work seamlessly behind the bar, juggling orders for their strongly-brewed drips and signature hot and cool beverages. While providing a wide selection of coffee specialties, pastries and various coffee related goods, patrons are invited to settle down in comfy armchairs and enjoy their favorite brews amid the chatter of the laidback yet caffeinated crowd.","doRecommend":"true","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/1822280/denver_co/starbucks.html"]}]

reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","text":"My daughter and myself had the best experience ever in your store at the Deli with a man named Josh. He was the best thing ever in that dept. He was so busy but he stopped and made each of us feel like we weren't taking up his time. He was so polite and helpful it was absolutely the best experience I have ever had in the store. He deserves a raise or at the minimal acknowledgement for a job greatly done with a smile and kindness. Josh really did make me feel like I mattered.Thank you Josh!!!!","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/king-soopers-6957611"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","date":"2010-10-09T00:00:00.000Z","text":"I use to work at the kingsooopers on evans for 7 months but i quit. I liked working there when i started and then after the 6th month it just went down hill. They love to give lots of hours with low pay. i use to work up to 45 hours in a week and only make 160 at the most so it sucked. The managers treat there employees like there just useless. I had a fellow employee that had requested two weeksoff 6 months ahead to go on a cruise. the week before she was about to leave they told her that she couldnt go they made her work. She wanted to quit but these times these days it is hard to find a job. Well all im saying is dont blame the employees blame the managers there the ones who run everything. quotquotI ALSO ENCOURAGE NO ONE TO WORK THEREquotquot","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/king-soopers-6957611"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","text":"NICE","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/king-soopers-6957611"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","date":"2009-08-01T00:00:00.000Z","text":"I used to love king soopers over all other grocers until I moved to a neighborhood where this location is the closest one to me. On numerous occasions it has been understaffed to a temper boiling level. One evening after I had packed my cart to the brim I arrive to the check out stands and there is not a single person at a register. I go find the lady working the quotquotself check outquotquot and her only response is quotquotoh, they're all on breakquotquot I ask when one will be back and she says ten minutes and that I could use the self check out! I don't even want to go into how annoying that was considering there is only so much space to place an item until you have to remove a bag and then everything stops till the lady presses an quotquotcontinuequotquot button from her computer. Oh and someone comes up to me and says quotquotYou have WAY too many items to be herequotquot and I said politely quotquotIm not here by choice mamnquotquot. She leaves. By the time I got home and about 20 other customers passed me by ALL, and I mean ALL of my frozen goods were thawed and drippy. Besides the understaffed issue, their shelves are understocked. Produce and meat are slim pickings all the time. The floors, carts, and everything always feel really dirty. I hate going to this place so much that I drive an extra 2 miles out of my way to avoid it when it's just 10 blocks away.","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/king-soopers-6957611"]}]

reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","text":"This business is possibly the worst I have ever had the displeasure to be with. They delivered water for my Costco plan, I had to have surgery and was not sure how much I would be home. I called to tell them I had 11 bottles and wanted to be put on hold . It seems (now) they don't have the option for hold so they said they shut me off for non-payment, I paid and ask they come pick up some of the 11 empty water bottles. Low and behold they no longer pick up the bottles and rack so they are harrassing me to pay for them and the plastic rack. I am trying to return them and their web page says they are closed, the phone number that you posted keeps hanging up on me. What to do","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/ds-waters-of-america-inc-470675914"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","text":"3 4 Fighting Parkinson's is sponsoring its 2nd annual bike ride, Pedaling 4 Parkinson's on June 4, 2011. Deep Rock Water Company has generously committed to be our official water sponsor. We are very grateful that Deep Rock is so involved with community events and is so willing to help us. On behalf of all of our riders, volunteers, and staff we thank you Deep Rock!","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/ds-waters-of-america-inc-470675914"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","text":"I am the co-race director of the Platte River 1/2 Marathon and Buckhorn Exchange Relay that was held 4/10/11. Deep Rock graciously donated enough water to keep 2600 runners hydrated with Colorado's best natural artesian water. Not only were our runners happy to drink this superior water, but as the race director my experience in working with the professional, friendly staff was nothing but pleasurable from start to finish. Thanks Deep Rock!","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/ds-waters-of-america-inc-470675914"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","text":"I am the site coordinator for the 9 health fair at Covenant Village of Colorado in Westminster, CO. The 9 health fair is a free and low cost health screening opportunity for the local community. For the past two years, Deep Rock Water has graciously donated enough water to quench the thirst of all of the participants at our site (last year 563, this year 626). They are very accomodating and willing to help out the local community. More companies should be as generous as Deep Rock Water! Thanks Deep Rock!","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/ds-waters-of-america-inc-470675914"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","date":"2011-06-04T00:00:00.000Z","text":"I am a fully disabled dying old man, Your Delivery Driver knows this. He came through our back sliding door, and knocked on my inside door to get my empty bottles. He then came into my room with the full bottles of Artesan Water. He was friendly, courteous, and professional in every way. Sometimes it is very hard for me to just live to just breath and move. Your Delivery Driver's small acts had a quotquotBid Impactquotquot on me. I would hope that he is rewarded in some way. Take in one of our Denver United Church Services on Sunday mornings. We meet on the DU campus at Sturm Hall. They greatly Bless me, as has... ...Your Extraordinaire Delivery Driver.","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/ds-waters-of-america-inc-470675914"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","text":"I use Deep Rock for both my business and my home and am always pleased with their service. The delivery staff are just great they're always friendly, address my staff by name, and make light conversation while they change out our water. The customer service team always checks in with us periodically to make sure we have everything we need which I think is a nice touch. I would reccommend Deep Rock to anyone and everyone!","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/ds-waters-of-america-inc-470675914"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","date":"2011-11-02T00:00:00.000Z","text":"First off, Deep Rock Water provides a superior product and I've never had an issue with poor customer service. That being said, their accounting department is a mess. They kept screwing up my bill, playing games with late fees, making math errors, double billing, failing to credit payments made, etc. Billing errors were so serious I canceled my account and paid the balance in full. Now I just got a past due notice on the account I closed several weeks ago -- fortunately I have my receipts. I do not know who is running their accounts receivable department, but it is hurting their business to allow such incompetence to continue. I would still be a customer if it wasn't for so many mistakes on my bill. At least I didn't sign up for auto-billing, because that would be a nightmare.","rating":2.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/ds-waters-of-america-inc-470675914"]}]

reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","text":"Sadly, Marczyk is not what it once was. They no longer provide the variety of or service for their cheeses. The butchers are apathetic. And their overall customer service is bordering on rude. This shop was once my favorite.","rating":2.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/marczyk-fine-foods-4504595"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","text":"Walking through downtown Denver up to Uptown was an interesting experience. I ended up at Marczyk, and I'm glad I did. This place is Gourmet and (sometimes) organic heaven. There was so much to choose from, I had no idea where to begin. I walked in, turned left, and looked that the various jam, jellies, relishes, breads (olive oil flatbreads What Sounds delicious). Then I wander ed over to the candy section for a special treat for myself. Lots of organic and international chocolate. I picked out some Hammond's Root Beer Drops and a Mocha truffle bar (with Pig's behind imprinted on it. You have to check it out) for my dad for his birthday. Good produce section, meat selection, and deli. I have a gigantic sweet tooth, and the dessert selection was unbelievable. There were individual cheesecakes and flans and mousses and cakes, but also big cakes for multiple people. If I had time to go back home before I went back to class, I would have bought a cheesecake for myself. Fresh bread selection, but also packaged wheat and organic selections. Nice looking baguettes. Yum. Marczyk Fine Foods equals Uptown Denver Heaven.","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/marczyk-fine-foods-4504595"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","date":"2008-11-04T00:00:00.000Z","text":"I go here specifically for the fresh seafood. The store displays it properly (not wrapped in plastic). The fish is always on ice or on a marble slab. It doesn't have that quotquotfishyquotquot smell. The staff is always really nice. I tried some of their cheeses for the first time and I wasn't disappointed. I don't do my regular shopping their, but use it when I want fresh fish or nice cheese.","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/marczyk-fine-foods-4504595"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","text":"I just bought two tenderloins and I loved them. I will be back and try some seafood next time. I really like the selection of candy for a small romantic dessert.","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/marczyk-fine-foods-4504595"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-05-19T00:00:00Z","text":"Alright, I'll admit it: I moved to Uptown for Marczyk's. It was on the top of the list of places in the neighborhood which looked hip enough for this east coast (Miami) transplant. Thankfully, the content lives up to the fascade! The folks at Marczyk's, from the owner to the butcher, are friendly and knowledgable. Though the selection may seem limited, this is not a supermarket. Each item is carefully chosen (in fact, when the chickens at the local egg farm went on strike, there was an apology note for having to sell what another big chain boutique market considers their quotquottop shelfquotquot eggs). Highlights include the cheese cave, butcher counter, and pre-made section (one of these days, though, this Miami native is going to have to show the Marczyks how to make maduros from plantains, rather than bananas). Though the produce section does generally leave something to be desired, the staff can usually make excellent suggestions to work around any ommissions in their stock. In all, Marzyk's is an incredible, around-the-corner neighborhood market. My frequent shopper rewards there are embarassingly large, so to say I recommend the place is an understatement.","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/marczyk-fine-foods-4504595"]}]

I had assumed until then that they were like a GNC. This was before they made quotquotNatural Grocersquotquot a prominent part of their name. At the time (this was several years ago) I had not yet embraced organic and whole foods. I remember thinking it was too small and quaint for my tastes. I did like their natural beauty section though! I've really changed since then. Now I will wait until they open to go without or go for coffee cream rather than King Sooper which is a little easier to get to. I have come to absolutely embrace the smaller store with the quiet lights - instead of wasting hours and money and ending up with a headache - I go, I know what I want, I don't buy more than I need, the experience is friendly, and yes, I have confidence that what I buy is the best available. Thank you VC for doing the work for me so I can get back to living. And we've found that we actually spend less every week which is counterintuitive being that most things are organic. I really think it is because we are buying more whole foods and cooking more. I also take advantage of their markdowns in fruit and dairy. Also their natural paper products and pet foods are less expensive. It's funny - we had eagerly anticipated the Sunflower Farmers Market to open in our area - but now that it is we only went a few times. Much too crowded and again, the feeling there is a lot of bait and switch - we always spend too much money on things we didn't really need or go in for. VC is an awesome little store (and so are others we've been to in the area). descriptions: [{"dateSeen":"2019-05-20T03:32:57Z","value":"Visit your neighborhood Safeway located at 10300 Federal Blvd, Federal Heights, CO, for a convenient and friendly grocery experience! reviews: [{"date":"2006-10-11T00:00:00.000Z","username":"by daphnesmom","rating":5.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"Forget your diet!","text":"Andre's pastries are out-of-this-world! I love their almond pastry, but so far haven't tried anything that isn't amazing. And for the high quality, the prices are quite reasonable. This is definitely THE place to ditch your diet!","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711754305/andres-restaurant-denver"]},{"date":"2004-09-17T00:00:00.000Z","username":"by colaila","rating":4.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"Lunch Favorite","text":"Yummy desserts and scrumptious lunches. What more can you ask for I love their Chicken Patties and the Pistachio Cake.","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711754305/andres-restaurant-denver"]},{"date":"2005-07-22T00:00:00.000Z","username":"by russiandianka","rating":5.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"You will never be disappointed!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!","text":"I have one thing to say, this is the best bakery in entire state. If you anywhere close, or even if you have to drive, give it a try.","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711754305/andres-restaurant-denver"]},{"date":"2006-12-11T00:00:00.000Z","username":"by MtnDenver","rating":5.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"Great dessert!","text":"This is a great weekend lunch spot! Lunch includes a drink like coffee or tea or soft drink, a main entree (choice of two), and your pick from the dessert tray. The food portions are not huge but quite filling, and the fare is swiss. The cheese quiche and beet salad were amazing. The line to sit down seemed long but moved very quickly. Rum cake was excellent as well. Plus this place has a general store section with a great selection of Swiss chocolate like Lindt. There is a parking lot also, which is convenient. Highly recommend!","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711754305/andres-restaurant-denver"]},{"date":"2009-06-24T00:00:00.000Z","username":"by writeon1","rating":4.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"Excellent, authentic and unique","text":"This is the Denver outpost of the original Andre's in Kansas City. The family has managed to keep it within a few cousins and there are three locations. The KC location is actually much larger and offers more than two selections for lunch per day, but aside from that, it's nice to see the principles being upheld in Denver. The prix-fixe lunch is always a treat, particularly because it includes the tempting dessert tray. Older people tend to flock here and are treated well by the staff. I particularly like it in the winter, when it feels cozy to be inside with a hearty meal, watching the snow coming down...There is also a bakery counter where one can indulge in all kinds of goodies to take home! I do wish that they would emulate the KC location and offer at least one vegetarian menu item per day.","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711754305/andres-restaurant-denver"]},{"date":"2009-01-03T00:00:00.000Z","username":"Angela P.","rating":4.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"Great choice for a girl's lunch.","text":"My book club stopped here for lunch before an event. They offer a delicious 10 lunch that includes a choice of 2 entrees, salad, veggies, beverage and dessert. The dessert features European pastries baked on the premises that are simply incredible. Service was great and we were in and out quickly. I heard that this place can get pretty crowded at lunchtime--we must have gotten there before the rush (11:15 am)","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711754305/andres-restaurant-denver"]},{"date":"2005-09-05T00:00:00.000Z","username":"by tablegum","rating":5.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"This is a treat!!!","text":"It may look crowded when you first walk in, but the wait line goes fast and shows you just how popular this little place is. Serving two menu items makes choices easy, especially when everything is so tasty. The dessert tray is my favorite part of the meal. Since I'm a Kansas City transplant, where the original Andre's opened in 1955, I was so very happy to see Andre's in Denver!!!","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711754305/andres-restaurant-denver"]}]

name: Common Grounds Downtown Coffee
reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2019-03-19T00:00:00Z","username":"david L.","date":"2015-08-31T00:00:00.000Z","text":"If you love coffee, you wouldn't get dissapointed with the quality of products you can get here. The best people the best coffee nothing less.","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/1822847/denver_co/common_grounds_downtown_coffee.html"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-03-19T00:00:00Z","username":"Harvestopal","date":"2011-10-04T00:00:00.000Z","text":"Never stepping foot back in there! EVER! I wouldn't even give it one star! I went in there and ALL I got was an attitude that made me turn right back out the door. I was so excited thinking I found an amazing little local coffee shop, a place where I could hold my meetings and do my girls nights, but once I got there and I got was attitude that made me walk right out the door. Seriously, if you want to support a local coffee shop, especially downtown there are several great ones who will actually treat you with kindness and respect, not a snooty attitude. I try to support my local cafe's but this is one place that did NOT make me feel comfortable. And ask anyone I am not one who usually complains. I will never ever go back.","doRecommend":"false","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/1822847/denver_co/common_grounds_downtown_coffee.html"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-03-19T00:00:00Z","username":"MikalKelly","date":"2011-08-10T00:00:00.000Z","text":"I love this coffee shop. I HATE the parfait. I really enjoy Common Grounds. I like all the people that work there, I like the decor, I really like the coffee and ice cream and sammichs. But I am SO PISSED right now at the stupid yogurt parfaits! First, the yogurt is delicious...it is...but the little dollop you get is ALL the way down at the bottom, underneath way too much heavy, chewy, RAISIN-LADEN granola that is completely impenetrable by any spoon I've ever tried (broken one plastic spoon after another), and some nice, fresh berries, which I'd LIKE to mix in my yogurt. You try eating this without a freaking bowl. Aint gonna happen!!","doRecommend":"true","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/1822847/denver_co/common_grounds_downtown_coffee.html"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-03-19T00:00:00Z","username":"saintm","date":"2008-09-13T00:00:00.000Z","text":"Two great Denver coffeehouses Common Grounds has two locations, and while different, they're both great examples of an urban coffee house. The Highlands location (the original) is still funky and comfortable, with sometimes wacky art and a variety of local musicians, and the Downtown location is convenient, cool, and absolutely non-corporate (hear that, Starbucks). I've always found the staff friendly at both shops, and they make great coffee. I've never found either place dirty, and if things are a little cluttered, its certainly because of the brisk business that Common Grounds does. You can't go wrong with Common Grounds.","doRecommend":"true","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/1822847/denver_co/common_grounds_downtown_coffee.html"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-03-19T00:00:00Z","username":"buffalochef","date":"2007-07-16T00:00:00.000Z","text":"2007 Review... I guess its easy to see that NOBODY has reviewed this spot for years. The reason, and I'm guessing here, bis we Highlanders are just too polite. Food Snob, never reviews bad spots. They just dont deserve mention. But, I need to check in here. I've been going to CG's since they opened. YEARS !!! For just the meeting of neighborhood friends. In all those years the owner has never said hi. Thats one ! Two... the place is dirty ! and 3, the coffee is just plain awful. Enough said. There are now 6 good coffee houses within walking distance and soon another. Who needs it. Get it together CGs !!!","doRecommend":"false","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/1822847/denver_co/common_grounds_downtown_coffee.html"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-03-19T00:00:00Z","username":"Contributor","date":"2006-05-31T00:00:00.000Z","text":"Excellent venue for the LoDo professional's tete-a-tete with friends and business colleagues. In ShortThe crisp decor here includes ornate suspended lighting fixtures, large front windows and dark woods used throughout. There's also bookshelves full of books and board games, bulletin boards advertising groovy events and an upright piano. All the food --pies, cakes, cookies, sandwiches, salads, quiches and breakfast burritos--comes from different vendors. But the real draw is the full coffee bar plus a fine selection of teas. The high-quality coffee is imported from Colorado's Breckenridge Coffee Roasters.","doRecommend":"true","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/1822847/denver_co/common_grounds_downtown_coffee.html"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-03-19T00:00:00Z","username":"the_knew_girl","date":"2004-07-09T00:00:00.000Z","text":"Just around the corner My boyfriend and I like to go here to get something yummy to drink and sit around and play games. That's the kind of thing you do at Common Grounds. It's a great hang-out spot where you don't have to worry if you're the prettiest person there or not. Try their hot chocolate!","doRecommend":"true","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/1822847/denver_co/common_grounds_downtown_coffee.html"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-03-19T00:00:00Z","username":"gypsytiger","date":"2003-01-14T00:00:00.000Z","text":"Keeping it local... Common Grounds has a great location, wonderful food with lots of choices (oh, the pies!), and good coffee to boot. Nice, quiet atmosphere during the day good for us book coffee lovers. BUT - they don't accept credit/debit cards. I rarely carry cash anymore, so sometimes I have to go somewhere else for my caffeine fix... Otherwise, this is definitely one of my local faves.","doRecommend":"true","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/1822847/denver_co/common_grounds_downtown_coffee.html"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-03-19T00:00:00Z","username":"spikerx","date":"2002-12-12T00:00:00.000Z","text":"making impact on coffee in denver! Common Grounds has consistently put forth great coffee for the common man. They work hard to maintain that funky coffee house atmosphere without raping your wallet for a great cupofjoy/joe...I dont often review but I drive 20 miles to buy their beans which they have only recently begun roasting themselves in small batches and the coffee couldnt be more fresh. I am really pleased with the small batch roast and the flavor consistency and the aroma of the organic sumatra is absolutely perfect.","doRecommend":"true","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/1822847/denver_co/common_grounds_downtown_coffee.html"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-03-19T00:00:00Z","username":"FarmerNed","date":"2002-10-31T00:00:00.000Z","text":"Uncommonly Bad Coffee Common Grounds is all about atmosphere--but not about good tasting coffee. Their espresso is horribly over roasted and bitter--which makes for terrible Americanos, Lattes, et al. Creepy old college professor types scope young women from behind their newspapers, while neighborhood yuppies line up for an average cuppa joe. The coffee jerks behind the counter are generally slow--the male ones, not the female ones. If you want a great cup of coffee with service to match, try Kaladi Bros. coffee near the University of Denver.","doRecommend":"false","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/1822847/denver_co/common_grounds_downtown_coffee.html"]}]

reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2019-03-18T00:00:00Z","username":"Contributor","date":"2009-01-06T00:00:00.000Z","text":"Treat the body like a temple at the country's first national certified organic market. In ShortWhole Foods is a vegetarian's dream grocery store, with a focus on natural and organic goods and a gargantuan selection of fruits, vegetables and vegan products. But carnivores won't feel neglected, as stores also boast a vast selection of top-quality meats, poultry and fish. Also expect fresh-baked goods, housewares, a floral department and a well-stocked vitamin and personal-product section. Deli offers hot and cold prepared foods and artisanal cheeses.","doRecommend":"true","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/45346623/denver_co/whole_foods_market.html"]}]

name: Tuscany Coffee Deli
reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2007-07-09T00:00:00.000Z","username":"gabe33","text":"I visit Tuscany Coffee most every morning. Their food and beverages are fantastic and so is their staff. Everyone there takes the time to learn your name and what you like to drink. It makes getting coffee a pleasurable experience - rather than some large chains that just try to rush you through with no personality. Tuscany is quick, quality, friendly service with excellent staff, food and drinks!","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/tuscany-coffee-deli-1810711"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2007-07-09T00:00:00.000Z","username":"cjr3","text":"Tuscany Coffee located in the lower level of the Wells Fargo Center is great!!! Im enjoying one of their delicious Americanos now One of the best things about Tuscany Coffee is the customer service. Ive been a customer for several years now and its because Phil, Amanda and everyone takes the time to know you. They have a serious following of regulars. They know my name and what I like. Sometimes my delicious beverage is ready before Ive paid. They have many food options from pastries to sandwiches to a great cheese enchilada soup. Tuscany Coffee is top notch! Go visit them and dont be surprised if you get a complimentary extra shot in your beverage and a new friend.","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/tuscany-coffee-deli-1810711"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2009-01-14T00:00:00.000Z","username":"CS5280","text":"If you are ever in Denver and want to treat your palette to the best cup of coffee, breakfast, lunch or anything on their menu, it will have the pleasure of tasting, then head down to either of the Tuscany Coffee's at 16th and Stout (across from Denvers south bound light rail) or 1700 Lincoln in the Wells Fargo Center (it's the cash register building). People who inquire of me about the coffee and food here I usually respond with the analogy of it is like comparing a Cadillac to a Chevy (not that Chevys are bad Ive owned a few myself, its just an analogy) when up against any of the myriad of coffee houses, which I have been to quite a few in different cities across the country and always find myself comparing coffee, sandwiches etc., to Tuscany. The ladies and gentlemen working the shop are the best you will encounter and will make you want to return! ENJOY, I do every chance I get!","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/tuscany-coffee-deli-1810711"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2010-12-19T00:00:00.000Z","username":"RedHookSalmon","text":"Great espresso drinks.. friendly customer service","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/tuscany-coffee-deli-1810711"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2007-07-19T00:00:00.000Z","username":"yogishe","text":"I've been a Tuscany customer for more than 7 years. They have the tastiest coffee roasts around, fresh pastry and fast, friendly service. Phil, the owner always greets you with a smile and does what it takes to keep his customers happy. Tuscany is a gem, if your down around 17th/Lincoln, give it a try!","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/tuscany-coffee-deli-1810711"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2011-08-03T00:00:00.000Z","username":"dougandsadie","text":"Tuscany serves the best coffee in Denver, their sandwiches are fabulous. Phil and his crew always greet you with a smile and an hello, very friendly atmosphere. Got to try their Cheesy Chicken Tortillas soup. Two great locations in the Denver metro area. Stop by and tell Phil hi.","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/tuscany-coffee-deli-1810711"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2011-07-31T00:00:00.000Z","username":"RedHukSalmon","text":"Great atmosphere inside the Wells Fargo building, you can sit down in the atrium and have a healthy or hearty meal while sipping your favorite espresso drink. Cant beat hand pressed espresso from talented baristas Gotta love a healthy sized vegetarian menu. Always great service and tunes. Check it out!","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/tuscany-coffee-deli-1810711"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2007-07-09T00:00:00.000Z","username":"z28missy","text":"I have been a customer of Tuscany Coffee for many years. I am hooked on the Americano, it is strong and rich, but not bitter. The quality of the coffee is superior to any of the larger chains. The staff is always friendly and attentive - sometimes my drink is ready before they have handed me my change! I also recommend the bacon, egg and cheese bagel for breakfast and the cheesy chicken enchilada soup for lunch - both are excellent. I consider myself a picky or discriminating consumer, and Tuscany has definitely met my high expectations. If you care about quality, then put Tuscany on your list!","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/tuscany-coffee-deli-1810711"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2007-07-09T00:00:00.000Z","username":"jsl","text":"Tuscany has great coffee, much better than Starbucks, which is good for them because no less than 6 Starbucks are within a short walk away. The Cafe also offers a number of breakfast and lunch items. They have very good baked goods (try the muffins and bagels), breakfast sandwiches (from a microwave, but very tasty), and deli meats (coffee doesnt go well with salami, but their fruity smoothie concoctions do). While the food is quite good, what keeps the regulars coming back in droves is a combination of expertly prepared, delicious espresso drinks and fast, friendly service. As a heavy espresso drinker, I feel confident in my estimation that Tuscany coffee is very high quality, better than all the surrounding competition. But the key here really is the service. Espresso just isnt the same when it comes from the push of a button and is handed over by someone who doesnt appreciate fine coffee. At Tuscany, every shot is hand prepared by baristas with extensive training. They really seem to enjoy serving coffee and they do it fast (I have seen them process huge lines of people with surprising speed and accuracy). If you are looking for a great first cup of joe, a quad shot to get you through a long meeting, or a full breakfast and lunch menu, all served up fast and fresh, Tuscany is your best shot in downtown.","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/tuscany-coffee-deli-1810711"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2007-07-18T00:00:00.000Z","username":"m3esq","text":"I have been a Tuscany regular since 1999, when I was working in the cash register building. Although I no longer work in that building, I will still go out of my way (past several Starbucks, a Dietrichs and Curious Coffee) just to get my morning coffee at Tuscany. It is just plain better, and the service is friendly and efficient. Phil, Amanda, and the rest of the crew take time to get to know your name and what you like. They have the best breakfast bagels (egg amp cheese) around, and the scones are always delicious. I even get my quotquothome brewquotquot coffee beans there, ground for french press. The Sienna (espresso roast) is awesome.","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/tuscany-coffee-deli-1810711"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2007-05-03T00:00:00.000Z","username":"deadragoo","text":"Good selection of breakfast pastries and bagels, okay coffee (really, starbucks is better) and TERRIBLE service and attitude. All of the emloyees look like they hate their job, and they reflect that back to the customer. I ordered an everything bagel with light cream cheese, and I got an onion bagel and very heavy cream cheese. Disappointing to say the least.","rating":2.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/tuscany-coffee-deli-1810711"]}]
