name: Common Grounds Coffeehouse
reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2011-08-10T00:00:00.000Z","username":"MikalKelly","text":"I really enjoy Common Grounds. I like all the people that work there, I like the decor, I really like the coffee and ice cream and sammichs. But I am SO PISSED right now at the stupid yogurt parfaits! First, the yogurt is delicious...it is...but the little dollop you get is ALL the way down at the bottom, underneath way too much heavy, chewy, RAISIN-LADEN granola that is completely impenetrable by any spoon I've ever tried (broken one plastic spoon after another), and some nice, fresh berries, which I'd LIKE to mix in my yogurt. You try eating this without a freaking bowl. Aint gonna happen!!","rating":3.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/common-grounds-coffeehouse-451668398"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2007-07-16T00:00:00.000Z","username":"buffalochef","text":"I guess its easy to see that NOBODY has reviewed this spot for years. The reason, and I'm guessing here, bis we Highlanders are just too polite. quotquotFood Snobquotquot, never reviews bad spots. They just dont deserve mention. But, I need to check in here. I've been going to CG's since they opened. YEARS !!! For just the meeting of neighborhood friends. In all those years the owner has never said quotquothiquotquot. Thats one ! Two... the place is dirty ! and 3, the coffee is just plain awful. Enough said. There are now 6 good coffee houses within walking distance and soon another. Who needs it. Get it together CGquotquots !!!","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/common-grounds-coffeehouse-451668398"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2003-01-14T00:00:00.000Z","username":"gypsytiger","text":"Common Grounds has a great location, wonderful food with lots of choices (oh, the pies!), and good coffee to boot. Nice, quiet atmosphere during the day good for us book amp coffee lovers. BUT - they don't accept credit/debit cards. I rarely carry cash anymore, so sometimes I have to go somewhere else for my caffeine fix... Otherwise, this is definitely one of my local faves.","rating":4.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/common-grounds-coffeehouse-451668398"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2004-07-09T00:00:00.000Z","username":"the_knew_girl","text":"My boyfriend and I like to go here to get something yummy to drink and sit around and play games. That's the kind of thing you do at Common Grounds. It's a great hang-out spot where you don't have to worry if you're the prettiest person there or not. Try their hot chocolate!","rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/common-grounds-coffeehouse-451668398"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2002-10-31T00:00:00.000Z","username":"FarmerNed","text":"Common Grounds is all about atmosphere--but not about good tasting coffee. Their espresso is horribly over roasted and bitter--which makes for terrible Americanos, Lattes, et al. Creepy old college professor types scope young women from behind their newspapers, while neighborhood yuppies line up for an average cuppa joe. The coffee jerks behind the counter are generally slow--the male ones, not the female ones. If you want a great cup of coffee with service to match, try Kaladi Bros. coffee near the University of Denver.","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/common-grounds-coffeehouse-451668398"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2011-10-04T00:00:00.000Z","username":"Harvestopal","text":"I wouldn't even give it one star! I went in there and ALL I got was an attitude that made me turn right back out the door. I was so excited thinking I found an amazing little local coffee shop, a place where I could hold my meetings and do my girls nights, but once I got there and I got was attitude that made me walk right out the door. Seriously, if you want to support a local coffee shop, especially downtown there are several great ones who will actually treat you with kindness and respect, not a snooty attitude. I try to support my local cafe's but this is one place that did NOT make me feel comfortable. And ask anyone I am not one who usually complains. I will never ever go back.","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/common-grounds-coffeehouse-451668398"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-31T00:00:00Z","date":"2008-09-13T00:00:00.000Z","username":"saintm","text":"Common Grounds has two locations, and while different, they're both great examples of an urban coffee house. The Highlands location (the original) is still funky and comfortable, with sometimes wacky art and a variety of local musicians, and the Downtown location is convenient, cool, and absolutely non-corporate (hear that, Starbucks). I've always found the staff friendly at both shops, and they make great coffee. I've never found either place dirty, and if things are a little cluttered, its certainly because of the brisk business that Common Grounds does. You can't go wrong with Common Grounds.","rating":4.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/common-grounds-coffeehouse-451668398"]}]

reviews: [{"date":"2008-08-04T00:00:00.000Z","username":"Anonymous P.","rating":4.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"Small store with a large heart so much selection!","text":"I like to try to eat a bit healthier, and I want to include my children and husband in that endeavor. This great little store near my home is very helpful in that. They have all sorts of organic and natural products in practically every conceivable category. Their selection of vitamins, minerals and supplements is mind-boggling. The staff are all so nice and helpful when you are looking for a particular item or just need a bit of advice on what to buy.","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711906450/vitamin-cottage-natural-grocer-lakewood"]},{"date":"2011-12-01T00:00:00.000Z","username":"Dan West","rating":5.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"Hate 'em","text":"They don't supply grocery bags. How arrogant.","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711906450/vitamin-cottage-natural-grocer-lakewood"]},{"date":"2008-09-07T00:00:00.000Z","username":"by beebalm","rating":5.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"Simplification and Less Is Better","text":"I remember the first time I went in - my partner had told me that it had a grocery store in the back. I had assumed until then that they were like a GNC. This was before they made Natural Grocers a prominent part of their name. At the time (this was several years ago) I had not yet embraced organic and whole foods. I remember thinking it was too small and quaint for my tastes. I did like their natural beauty section though! I've really changed since then. Now I will wait until they open to go without or go for coffee cream rather than King Sooper which is a little easier to get to. I have come to absolutely embrace the smaller store with the quiet lights - instead of wasting hours and money and ending up with a headache - I go, I know what I want, I don't buy more than I need, the experience is friendly, and yes, I have confidence that what I buy is the best available. Thank you VC for doing the work for me so I can get back to living. And we've found that we actually spend less every week which is counterintuitive being that most things are organic. I really think it is because we are buying more whole foods and cooking more. I also take advantage of their markdowns in fruit and dairy. Also their natural paper products and pet foods are less expensive. It's funny - we had eagerly anticipated the Sunflower Farmers Market to open in our area - but now that it is we only went a few times. Much too crowded and again, the feeling there is a lot of bait and switch - we always spend too much money on things we didn't really need or go in for. VC is an awesome little store (and so are others we've been to in the area). Thanks for helping us meet our goals of simplifying our life so we can get back to doing what we enjoy...living our life!","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711906450/vitamin-cottage-natural-grocer-lakewood"]}]

name: Pacific Mercantile Company
reviews: [{"date":"2010-04-02T00:00:00.000Z","username":"Ann C.","rating":5.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"Asian grocery","text":"No better place to buy great Asian groceries. I love to buy gifts of ceramics and lacquer here, and origami books and supplies.","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711757936/pacific-mercantile-company-denver"]},{"date":"2010-03-13T00:00:00.000Z","username":"Julie H.","rating":5.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"LoDo treasure!","text":"Pacific Mercantile carries so many of the Pacific Rim foods my husband misses from Hawaii. You can find Japanese, Chinese, Vietnamese, Thai, Philippino, Korean, Hawaiian, and more treats. Frozen, fresh, refrigerated and dry ingredients. Also a wonderful section of tableware, kitchen items, and origami paper.","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711757936/pacific-mercantile-company-denver"]},{"date":"2009-09-09T00:00:00.000Z","username":"Aleece K.","rating":5.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"A fabulous source for asian and hawaiian foods","text":"I found out about Pacific Mercantile while lamenting to a friend about how much I missed Angelo Pietro's salad dressings from Hawaii. That's just the beginning of what this incredibly convenient asian supermarket has to offer. From fresh vegetables like daikon radishes to sweet rice bean cakes or li hing moi. Aisles of noodles and sauces and freezers full of a variety of traditional asian dishes.","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711757936/pacific-mercantile-company-denver"]},{"date":"2009-07-05T00:00:00.000Z","username":"by Kcastro7","rating":5.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"Fish!","text":"I LOVE sushi. I used to have to drive to Aurora to find sushi grade fish but now.........Pacific Mercantile has the best selection of fresh sushi grade fish.Thats saying a whole bunch since we are obviously nowhere near a coast. FISH FISH, FISH!!!","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711757936/pacific-mercantile-company-denver"]},{"date":"2009-07-01T00:00:00.000Z","username":"by aimeewoods","rating":5.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"BEST customer service!","text":"I actually placed an order online for this store since they are the only supplier I have found of pineapple mochi and Dekavita C from Japan. There was a problem emailing their customer service when I needed to change my shipping options but when I called the store, they immediately found my order and shipped it the same day. The woman I spoke with was unbelievably nice and helpful. I will definitely be a repeat customer!","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711757936/pacific-mercantile-company-denver"]},{"date":"2002-12-19T00:00:00.000Z","username":"by popijam","rating":4.0,"dateSeen":"2019-02-23T00:00:00Z","title":"Great for all of us!","text":"Unlike many cities on the west coast, Denver doesn't have an especially significant population of oriental Asians. However, we have a little eastern gem in our cow town chock full of caucasian, african and latin americans. Even a gaijin (somewhat derogatory Japanese slang for us predominant round eyes) like myself is welcome, comfortable, and excited to shop at Pacific mercantile. If you're cooking an Asian meal and need ingredients/supplies you just can't find at the yup stores (e.g. Whole Foods, Wild Oats - don't get me wrong, I shop there too), then mosey on over here. Note that it's in the same 'hood as Akebono, a nice Japanese/sushi restaurant at Sakura Square. Patronize diversity, support choice, and try something different!","sourceURLs":["http://www.insiderpages.com/b/3711757936/pacific-mercantile-company-denver"]}]

descriptions: [{"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/lakewood-co/mip/safeway-473514323"],"value":"Visit your neighborhood Safeway located at 9160 W Colfax Ave, Lakewood, CO, for a convenient and friendly grocery experience! From our bakery and deli, to fresh produce and helpful pharmacy staff, weve got you covered! Our bakery features customizable cakes, cupcakes and more while the deli offers a variety of party trays, made to order. At the butcher-block youll find an assortment of meat and seafood, even offering sushi in select locations, while the produce department is full of fresh fruits and veggies galore! Shop the floral department for exclusive debi lily design products and services and stop by the pharmacy for specialty care, including immunizations, prescription refills and so much more! Safeway is dedicated to being your one-stop-shop and provides an in-store bank, Coin Star system, and Western Union service in select locations! Further enhance your shopping experience by grabbing a hot cup of coffee at your in-store Starbucks or Seattles Best Drip Coffee and enjoy renting a movie from Redbox. Check out our Weekly Ad for store savings, earn Gas Rewards with purchases and download our Safeway app for just for U personalized offers. For more information, stop by or call (303) 232-4989. Our service will make Safeway your favorite local supermarket!","dateSeen":"2019-01-31T05:09:00.000Z"}]

descriptions: [{"sourceURLs":["https://www.yellowpages.com/denver-co/mip/giambrocco-produce-co-3389626"],"value":"In 1933, Joe Giambrocco went into business for himself as a produce peddler. He bought a 1930 Fargo truck, filled it with produce bought at the Cherry Creek Market and began a door-to-door route. Today, that company is known as Giambrocco Food Service. The company has more than 24 trucks, several state of the art ripening rooms, four bay receiving docks, an in-house mechanic, nearly five separately-controlled coolers and 3,330 square feet of freezer storage space in its warehouse. Giambrocco is a wholesale distributor of food service items including fresh, frozen and canned-food products paper products janitorial supplies spices and baking supplies. Its customers come from food-service establishments such as restaurants, day-care facilities, lunchrooms and cafeterias. Giambrocco services the Denver area.","dateSeen":"2019-01-31T03:33:00.000Z"}]

name: Chez Cheese Gourmet Market
reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2019-01-22T00:00:00Z","username":"mesimos","date":"2009-02-27T00:00:00.000Z","text":"Amazing food shop with high quality products, excellent service, international flavor Chez Cheese is an amazing shop. Don't let the name fool you. It's more than just an awesome selection of fine cheeses and meats (which Don, the owner, will gladly let you taste before you purchase). They have a solid selection of spreads, dips, mustards, oils, olives, jams, jellies, etc. The fridge has fresh eggs, mascarpone, yogurt, soy milk, reg milk, creamer, juices. At Christmas, they had great eggnogg. There's a great selection of pastas, sauce, herb-infused tomato paste. Crackers, chips. Whole beans for coffee. Fresh breads daily. Fruits and veggies (with more in the back if you can't find what you are looking for). It's an amazing shop. Do yourself the favor and stop in. And last but not least, Don does a neat variety of gourmet grilled cheeses!","doRecommend":"true","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/43324028/denver_co/chez_cheese_gourmet_market.html"]},{"dateSeen":"2019-01-22T00:00:00Z","username":"hypechic34","date":"2008-09-19T00:00:00.000Z","text":"Mini Market in the Heart of Downtown I wish I had some spare change because I would spnd it here for some fine delicacies. It's the closet thing to a grocery store in LoDo for the time being, unfortunately. If you live downtown and don't have a car, try checking this place out. Unfortunately, you'll still have to schlepp your behind to the King Soopers in Capitol Hill or 14th and Speer for essentials like toilet paper, but oh well. To indulge in some gourmet tastes, come here. They serve up some gourmet cheeses (hence the name), but there's so much more. I wanted to buy so much here. but sadly, I walked out empty handed. What I wanted to try was some jalepeno relish (how delicious would that be on some franks). There were many delicious looking fruit jams, spreads, and jellies. Prefect for a party or just a night at home watching movies. Also tasty crackers and chips (perhaps organic). I also wanted to try the assorted set of stuffed olives or maybe give them as s gift. The one that stood out to me was Cajun stuffed olives. YUM The store also has a small selection of produce, but it looked a bit sad. If you need an apple in the middle day, come here to pick one up. It's worth a try, I suppose. Friendly service, always a plus in my book. Chez Cheese is worth checking out if your palette calls for only pricey, gourmet nutrients.","doRecommend":"true","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/43324028/denver_co/chez_cheese_gourmet_market.html"]}]

In ShortGourmet heaven awaits at this small shop filled with exceptional treats. Find more than 35 varieties of cheese, imported from around the world, aged with care and then rotated until ripe and ready for purchase. Caviar, honeys, oils, vinegars and olives, fresh breads and chocolates are all the elite of their ilk. You'll also find imported pastas, jams, dried mushrooms and herbs that aren't available at other markets. And yes, there are truffles, too.","doRecommend":"true","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/profile/11494320/denver_co/the_truffle.html"]}]

reviews: [{"username":"Patrick Jones","date":"2014-07-16T00:00:00.000Z","title":"Fell Scammed and Cheated (Non-Profit)","dateSeen":"2018-12-04T00:00:00Z","text":"I dont normally write up negative reviews, unless it's truly deserving and really hope the owners see this and make corrective practices. ||[]||[]I bought a Rancilio and wanted them to service it. I run a small non-profit and dropping off the machine to them was to take 1-2 weeks, but for a fee they could come out and work on it. ||[] ||[]||[]There person (I know his name, just leaving it out) showed up, turned it on, and everything was working swell.. unless the bar pressure didnt stop climbing and the safety valve blew off. Happened twice. I was told it was a bad temp sensor or logic board. Cheapest option was the Temp Sensor at $80. So I had them order it. Suppose to come 2-3 day, and after a week I called, 2 weeks I called, and the 3rd week I left a message to make sure they canceled my order and made sure they didnt charge me for the part, told them my complaint, and still no call back... ||[]||[]The sad part is, ME and inexperienced person, with no knowledge googled and found the fix in 10 mins. All the service person had to do was adjust the potentiometer to stop at the desired bar pressure... That's it... instead, the safety valve blew, trash.. and it cost me $150 to have them out, and they billed me for a gasket which wasn't the right one, because they didnt have one on the truck... when then knew they were coming out for... $150 and i got a gasket which isn't the raight one. Again, I hope this company fixes the issue, cause Im out $150 for installing a wrong gasket and to be told they would need to order additional parts when they should have just adjusted the only screw on the logic board. I feel ripped off and scammed.","rating":1.0,"sourceURLs":["http://www.yellowbook.com/profile/stans-frozen-food_1861383820.html"]}]

Cantonese cuisine is known for Dim Sum (Yum Cha), and seafood dishes. This place has consistently wonderful food, and though the atmosphere is a little dingy and run down, I have learned over time that those places usually have the best food. As long as the focus is in the kitchen, I don't really care what the front of the house looks like. Service has always been great, and we've become regulars over the last two years. We're always w...view moreelcomed and well taken care of. You can also call in for take out, and can also get bulk roast pork or duck to take home. The dim sum is wonderful, and served 7 days a week. Chow Fun, Hong Kong Style Wonton Soup, Stir Fried Egg and Tomato, and their Brisket and Tendon hotpot is sure to please. This is not a place for egg foo young or sweet and sour pork. You can get authentic Cantonese food (whole steamed fish, Am Choy, salt and pepper shrimp) at a very reasonable price, and brush up on your cantonese language skills. Don't be afraid to experiment and try something new, you'll probably like it, and also, don't be afraid to ask for something you've had somewhere else if it's not on the menu, they'll be happy to try and make it for you. descriptions: [{"value":"Healthy Living for Less!","dateSeen":"2016-06-10T22:11:19Z","sourceURLs":["https://foursquare.com/v/sprouts-farmers-market/49e1261cf964a5209c611fe3"]},{"dateSeen":"2017-03-03T22:01:47Z","value":"Sprouts is the grocery shopping experience that makes healthy living easy and affordable. Our bright and cheery neighborhood grocery stores offer fresh, natural and organic foods and products at incredible prices - and in an approachable setting that feels like an old-fashioned farmers market. You'll find mountains of colorful, fresh fruits and vegetables, barrels of wholesome grains, nuts and sweets, and full-service deli, meat and seafood counters-complete with handmade burgers and sausages. Roam around our spacious, low-profile aisles and you'll find fresh baked goods, tasty and convenient, ready-to-eat meals, gourmet cheeses, sensibly-priced vitamins and supplements, and thousands of natural, organic and gluten-free groceries. Visit your local Sprouts today in Denver, CO!","sourceURLs":["http://www.superpages.com/bp/denver-co/sprouts-farmers-market-L0143460093.htm"]}]

reviews: [{"date":"2014-05-18T00:00:00Z","username":"ron.beall.5","dateSeen":"2016-02-09T00:00:00Z","text":"You know, to pick on only this store's employee in this day and age and not acknowledge that service employs at most store suck would not be fair. Sorry I asked you a question and made you have to actually work. I would have not made you get someone, that does understand the importance of a customer, if you would of least tried to help...view more me and not give me a made answer and hoped I go away. Next, Kelly the so called manager, comes out from wherever she is and promises to call me when you get some damn almonds, she never did, I did not think she would. What a lame manager. The girl with the tatoo on her face has to be the worst store employee ever. If you hate your job quit, do not take it out on you employers customers. I found almonds online, one less thing to buy from your store. I try to do a little shopping as I can in you rude store. I hope we get another store like yours close by so I never have to go there again. You truly do suck. Ronview less","sourceURLs":["http://www.yellowpages.com/south-hill-va/mip/freedom-life-fitness-607293"],"rating":1.0},{"title":"Startlingly mediocre","username":"writeon1","text":"I was excited to find out that there was a little competition to Whole Foods (which I love) but have been disappointed with nearly every excursion I've made to Sunflower Market. The produce has a good mix of organic and un-organic items but most of the fruit is covered with flies and tends to be spoiled and bruised. I will never buy berries there again after my last experience. Also, why isn't there a deli for made-to-order sandwiches And why is there all that candy that is just mains...view moretream and filled with chemicals Boar's Head meats are not special, nor do they necessarily use natural ingredients. You really have to continue to scrutinize labels at Sunflower. Given a choice, I'll stick with Whole Foods!view less","dateSeen":"2016-02-09T00:00:00Z","date":"2009-06-22T00:00:00Z","sourceURLs":["http://www.yellowpages.com/south-hill-va/mip/freedom-life-fitness-607293"],"rating":2.0}]

descriptions: [{"dateSeen":"2017-02-16T21:47:00.000Z","value":"Sprouts is the grocery shopping experience that makes healthy living easy and affordable. Our bright and cheery neighborhood grocery stores offer fresh, natural and organic foods and products at incredible prices - and in an approachable setting that feels like an old-fashioned farmers market. You'll find mountains of colorful, fresh fruits and vegetables, barrels of wholesome grains, nuts and sweets, and full-service deli, meat and seafood counters-complete with handmade burgers and sausages. Roam around our spacious, low-profile aisles and you'll find fresh baked goods, tasty and convenient, ready-to-eat meals, gourmet cheeses, sensibly-priced vitamins and supplements, and thousands of natural, organic and gluten-free groceries. Visit your local Sprouts today in Denver, CO!","sourceURLs":["http://www.superpages.com/bp/denver-co/sprouts-farmers-market-L2601024640.htm"]}]

descriptions: [{"value":"Healthy Chef Express is a chef-owned company, working with local and regional ingredients, to provide natural healthy meals.The meals provided are a combination of 40% good carbohydrates, from fresh fruits and vegetables, 30% protein from lean meat, fish, cheese, and other healthy proteins and 30% favorable fats such as sesame oil, avocados, and omega-3s. A full meal set includes breakfast, lunch, dinner, and a snack, which provides 1200 - 1600 calories for women and 1,600 - 2,000 calories for men.At Healthy Chef Express, we understand that diet is only one of several areas that must be in balance for an optimum healthy lifestyle. These meals work in conjunction with your current fitness plan, to maximize your results.In addition to the obvious health benefits of the plan, imagine not having to shop for food, cook a meal, or clean your kitchen? Our service provides healthy & balanced meals prepared by our award-winning chef & delivered fresh to your door.\\"I started having Healthy Chef Express delivered when I was in the middle of undergoing chemotherapy. It was so wonderful to have delicious, healthy meals delivered every day. The menu is incredibly diverse and my favorite part of the day was always opening the cooler of food to see my menu for the next few days. During a time when I didn't have the energy to think about or plan meals, it was such a gift to have Healthy Chef Express!\\" - Susan, Denver","dateSeen":"2017-02-26T20:17:00.000Z","sourceURLs":["http://www.superpages.com/bp/lakewood-co/healthy-chef-express-L2215369463.htm"]}]

reviews: [{"dateSeen":"2014-12-03T00:00:00Z","username":"getmamou","date":"2007-02-02T06:00:00Z","text":"I was eating WHAT from Whole Foods!!! Don't go to Vitamin Cottage if you are alread sqeemish about chemicals in food. What you will find out (whether you want to or not) is that they won't sell most of what the other grocers tell is you is good for you, because it really isn't. Whole Foods will never feel as groovy again after someone here tells you what WF puts in their salads and deli items to keep it fresh. These guys seem to really trod the straight and narrow (dogmatic) when it comes to the clean food movement. Still, they had what I needed plus a ton of new things I had never seenin an organic version. I also left with a handful of (free) nutrition sheets the staff gave out when I asked some questions. Cheap I could get the same stuff in non-organic for less at the other stores, but for the identical items they seem like their prices are far below Kings. Compared to Whole Foods its like, uh, free. Baristas over Buttons","username":"RedHookSalmon","dateSeen":"2016-05-14T00:00:00Z","date":"2010-12-18T00:00:00Z","text":"Great espresso drinks.. friendly customer service","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/review/1826608%2525253FreviewId%2525253D480126129","http://www.yellowpages.com/richland-ms/mip/waffle-house-1810711"],"rating":5.0},{"dateSeen":"2016-05-14T00:00:00Z","username":"CS5280","title":"The best coffee and eatery around...","date":"2009-01-13T00:00:00Z","text":"If you are ever in Denver and want to treat your palette to the best cup of coffee, breakfast, lunch or anything on their menu, it will have the pleasure of tasting, then head down to either of the Tuscany Coffee's at 16th and Stout (across from Denvers south bound light rail) or 1700 Lincoln in the Wells Fargo Center (it's the cash register building). People who inquire of me about the coffee and food here I usually respond with the analogy of it is like comparing a Cadillac to a Ch...view moreevy (not that Chevys are bad Ive owned a few myself, its just an analogy) when up against any of the myriad of coffee houses, which I have been to quite a few in different cities across the country and always find myself comparing coffee, sandwiches etc., to Tuscany. The ladies and gentlemen working the shop are the best you will encounter and will make you want to return! ENJOY, I do every chance I get!view less","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/review/1826608%2525253FreviewId%2525253D479489137","http://www.yellowpages.com/richland-ms/mip/waffle-house-1810711"],"rating":5.0},{"date":"2007-07-17T00:00:00Z","username":"m3esq","text":"I have been a Tuscany regular since 1999, when I was working in the cash register building. Although I no longer work in that building, I will still go out of my way (past several Starbucks, a Dietrichs and Curious Coffee) just to get my morning coffee at Tuscany. It is just plain better, and the service is friendly and efficient. Phil, Amanda, and the rest of the crew take time to get to know your name and what you like. They have the best breakfast bagels (egg cheese) around, a...view morend the scones are always delicious. I even get my home brew coffee beans there, ground for french press. The Sienna (espresso roast) is awesome.view less","title":"Great coffee!","dateSeen":"2016-05-14T00:00:00Z","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/review/1826608%2525253FreviewId%2525253D478031216","http://www.yellowpages.com/richland-ms/mip/waffle-house-1810711"],"rating":5.0},{"date":"2007-07-08T00:00:00Z","text":"Tuscany has great coffee, much better than Starbucks, which is good for them because no less than 6 Starbucks are within a short walk away. The Cafe also offers a number of breakfast and lunch items. They have very good baked goods (try the muffins and bagels), breakfast sandwiches (from a microwave, but very tasty), and deli meats (coffee doesnt go well with salami, but their fruity smoothie concoctions do). While the food is quite good, what keeps the regulars coming back in drov...view morees is a combination of expertly prepared, delicious espresso drinks and fast, friendly service. As a heavy espresso drinker, I feel confident in my estimation that Tuscany coffee is very high quality, better than all the surrounding competition. But the key here really is the service. Espresso just isnt the same when it comes from the push of a button and is handed over by someone who doesnt appreciate fine coffee. At Tuscany, every shot is hand prepared by baristas with extensive training. They really seem to enjoy serving coffee and they do it fast (I have seen them process huge lines of people with surprising speed and accuracy). If you are looking for a great first cup of joe, a quad shot to get you through a long meeting, or a full breakfast and lunch menu, all served up fast and fresh, Tuscany is your best shot in downtown.view less","username":"jsl","dateSeen":"2016-05-14T00:00:00Z","title":"Best espresso around","sourceURLs":["http://www.citysearch.com/review/1826608%2525253FreviewId%2525253D478031213","http://www.yellowpages.com/richland-ms/mip/waffle-house-1810711"],"rating":5.0},{"text":"I visit Tuscany Coffee most every morning.
